<article>
    <h1>From the run&#xAD;way to so&#xAD;cial me&#xAD;dia plat&#xAD;forms</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200814/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-14"><time>2020-08-14</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Amanda Chai</span>
    </section>

    <p>The on­line world may no longer be new fron­tier for Burberry, but how do other lux­ury brands stack up?</p>
    <p>Buck­ing the tra­di­tion of re­sis­tance, more have be­gun to em­brace the on­line space.</p>
    <p>In re­cent years, sev­eral lux­ury brands have opened flag­ship on­line stores on Tmall, the Alibaba Group’s busi­ness-to-cus­tomer mar­ket­place. Prada and Miu Miu joined in March this year.</p>
    <p>The pan­demic has only ac­cel­er­ated the lux­ury in­dus­try’s grad­ual em­brac­ing of dig­i­tal­i­sa­tion.</p>
    <p>Here are three brands which flirted promi­nently with dig­i­tal medi­ums this year.</p>
    <p>CHANEL</p>
    <p>Orig­i­nally in­tended to be show­cased in Capri, Italy, the Chanel Cruise 2020/21 col­lec­tion, Balade en Mediter­ra­nee, was un­veiled dig­i­tally on June 8 on chanel.com and its so­cial me­dia plat­forms.</p>
    <p>It is a no­table move for the brand, of­ten revered for its ex­trav­a­gantly staged fash­ion shows that have taken place in set­tings rang­ing from a sandy beach to a win­try land­scape with a real ice­berg flown in from Scan­di­navia.</p>
    <p>DIOR</p>
    <p>The French fash­ion house swopped its usual run­way show at the can­celled Paris Cou­ture Week for a whim­si­cal, 10-minute short film show­cas­ing looks from its Fall/Win­ter 2020 haute cou­ture line, which pre­miered on July 6 on Dior’s web­site.</p>
    <p>Directed by award-win­ning Ital­ian di­rec­tor Mat­teo Gar­rone, the short fea­tured looks from the col­lec­tion at minia­ture scale, weav­ing them into the fan­tasy film’s story.</p>
    <p>GUCCI</p>
    <p>On July 17, cre­ative di­rec­tor Alessan­dro Michele pre­sented his Epi­logue col­lec­tion via a 12-hour live-stream­ing event.</p>
    <p>Pre­mier­ing in the form of a 20-minute vis­ual nar­ra­tive fea­ture, it was broad­cast on the last day of the in­au­gu­ral Mi­lan Dig­i­tal Fash­ion Week, on dig­i­tal plat­forms in­clud­ing Gucci.com, YouTube, In­sta­gram, Facebook and Weibo.</p>
    <p>More in­ter­est­ingly, the bulk of the live stream was live footage from the set of Gucci’s ad­ver­tis­ing cam­paign shoot in Rome – giv­ing view­ers a rare peek behind the scenes of a fash­ion shoot.</p>

